# Vectorized extraction of lowercase words using the cudf.pandas extension
# Split each listing name into words, flatten into one word per row, lowercase, then collect into a Python list
tmp = (
    airbnb.name
        .str.split()   # split each listing name into a list of words
        .explode()     # flatten the lists into individual word entries
        .str.lower()   # lowercase every word
)
# Convert the resulting Series to a PyArrow array and then to a native Python list
names_for_count_ = tmp.to_arrow().to_pylist()

Reason: Replacing the final `.tolist()` (which can trigger ambiguous boolean comparisons on cudf objects) with an explicit conversion via `.to_arrow().to_pylist()` ensures that we end up with a plain Python list of strings. This works robustly on both cudf and pandas Series and avoids the ValueError caused by trying to interpret a Series/DataFrame as a boolean during the equality assertions.
